title: Jacob Knyspel
text: I’m currently a PhD student in Behavioural Genetics at King’s College London, funded by a studentship from the KCL MRC DTP. I’m especially interested in improving phenotypic specificity in behavioural genetics research through the implementation of multivariate statistical methods such as network analysis and structural equation modelling.
